WEBVTT

00:00.209 --> 00:02.677
We can't have you showing up
for the Battle of Saratoga

00:02.678 --> 00:04.980
missing a button, can we?

00:04.981 --> 00:07.249
There we are.

00:07.250 --> 00:10.518
Oh.

00:11.821 --> 00:15.993
Betsy Ross herself would envy
your handiwork, Miss Caroline.

00:16.192 --> 00:21.932
I made you some new shirts,
breeches and hose,

00:21.933 --> 00:24.882
all cut from cloth woven
on a heritage Saxony loom.

00:24.883 --> 00:26.268
- Oh.
- (laughs)

00:26.269 --> 00:29.519
I also brought you butter
I churned last night

00:29.520 --> 00:31.067
and some lingonberry preserves.

00:31.068 --> 00:33.542
And...

00:33.543 --> 00:35.677
Oh, Miss Caroline.

00:35.678 --> 00:38.531
Your generosity knows no bounds.

00:38.532 --> 00:40.933
I shall treasure these gifts.

00:40.934 --> 00:44.336
I've never met anyone
like you before, Ichabod.

00:44.337 --> 00:46.972
Your dedication to Colonial reenactment

00:46.973 --> 00:49.408
is so impressive.

00:49.409 --> 00:50.710
You never break character...

00:50.711 --> 00:53.060
Well, one might say it's a way of life.

00:53.061 --> 00:54.080
I think it's inspiring,

00:54.081 --> 00:58.050
and to be honest, kind of... attractive.

00:58.952 --> 01:00.419
Oh.

01:00.420 --> 01:04.271
Uh, Miss Caroline, words cannot
express how flattered I am.

01:04.272 --> 01:05.838
Then don't use words.

01:05.839 --> 01:07.506
I'm a married man.

01:07.507 --> 01:10.009
Oh.

01:10.010 --> 01:12.611
(sighs) I'm so sorry.

01:12.612 --> 01:14.513
- No...
- You live alone, you never talk about her.

01:14.514 --> 01:15.890
There's no photos of her around.

01:15.891 --> 01:17.359
I assumed you were single

01:17.360 --> 01:19.227
or separated or a widower.

01:19.228 --> 01:23.064
No... I assure you my
wife is alive and well.

01:23.065 --> 01:25.066
(door opens)

01:26.969 --> 01:29.104
Didn't mean to interrupt.

01:29.105 --> 01:30.972
I am such an idiot. This is not

01:30.973 --> 01:32.607
what it looks like, Mrs. Crane.

01:32.608 --> 01:34.209
- Mrs. who now?
- Oh!

01:34.210 --> 01:37.579
No, no, uh, Miss Mills is my partner.

01:37.580 --> 01:38.980
Uh, not-not life partner.

01:38.981 --> 01:41.649
She's my... We... Oh, look!

01:41.650 --> 01:44.619
She comes bearing a selection
of delicacies from the Far East.

01:44.620 --> 01:46.755
Commonly known as Yummy Food Schezuan.

01:46.756 --> 01:48.690
I'll be going now. Excuse me.

01:48.691 --> 01:50.992
- Oh, Miss Caroline. Please...
- Thanks.

01:52.228 --> 01:55.030
We need a signal.

01:55.031 --> 01:56.953
Need to hang a tie on the
doorknob or something.

01:56.954 --> 01:57.832
(laughs)

01:57.833 --> 02:00.001
Lieutenant, you are making light

02:00.002 --> 02:01.703
of a very uncomfortable situation.

02:01.704 --> 02:04.172
I was regretfully unaware

02:04.173 --> 02:07.393
of Miss Caroline's...
affections... for me.

02:07.394 --> 02:08.701
Ah. Anyone could tell

02:08.702 --> 02:10.786
that girl had a case
of Crane on the brain.

02:10.834 --> 02:13.948
Well... I have had much

02:13.949 --> 02:15.884
weighing on my mind, so...

02:15.885 --> 02:18.753
It's Katrina. You're worried about her.

02:18.754 --> 02:22.103
Thoughts of my wife in
peril do plague me.

02:22.104 --> 02:22.857
Look...

02:22.858 --> 02:25.493
she chose to stay with
the Horseman, Crane.

02:26.328 --> 02:28.196
She can handle herself.

